==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iolite
<hw>I"o*lite</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'i`on</grk> a violet + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A silicate of alumina, iron, and magnesia, having
a bright blue color and vitreous luster; cordierite. It is remarkable
for its dichroism, and is also called <altname>dichroite</altname>. A
variety called <stype>Caribbean iolite</stype> has a lighter blue
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Io moth</ent>⟦br⟧
